cs.CV, cs.MM, cs.LG, cs.GR, cs.AI 

This paper deals with fashion image inpainting, which involves generating missing parts of an image while ensuring visual compatibility with the existing fashion garments. This task falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The proposed method involves disentangling the generation of shape and appearance, which is a common technique in generative modeling (cs.MM). The authors also introduce two encoders interacting with one another to learn latent code in a shared compatibility space, which involves learning representations and optimizing them jointly, a technique commonly used in machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also involves fashion analysis and transfer, which falls under the graphics (cs.GR) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories.
